newsitem.title: USA: FCOJ futures end choppy session lower.
newsitem.headline: FCOJ futures end choppy session lower.

text.p: Frozen concentrated orange juice futures ended weaker Wednesday, pressured by a late-session round of speculative selling, traders said.
Active November FCOJ settled 1.40 cents a lb lower, at 105.80, having ranged from 107.90 to 105.25. The remaining months closed down 0.25 to 0.90.
One trader said light sell-stops were triggered near 107.00 cents in the December contract, but the market failed to gather enough downward momentum to spark much follow-through selling.
Technically, traders pegged November support at 104-103 cents, while resistance was seen at 110-112.
Dealers said the session was generally uneventful, with volume reaching only an estimated 1,500 lots.
"It did not go anywhere, it was trapped in a tight range." one analyst said.
Traders await the USDA's Florida crop estimate in about six weeks for fundamental direction. Expectations for the crop remain around 215 million 90-lb boxes.
"The estimate is important because it is the first by the USDA," the analyst said.
